Be Fit Food, victorious in the 2018 Victorian Telstra Business of the Year and the 2022 Championing Health in Victoria Award, is transforming Australia's health with real wholefood alternatives. With over 3 million meals sold and $32.1 million revenue in 5 years, they are challenging the synthetic diet industry.

Back their journey and join this vibrant success story.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Be Fit Food’s vision is to change the health of Australia one bite at a time by providing a real wholefood alternative to the synthetic diet shakes and bars industry.

The company specifically targets health improvement, addressing lifestyle health issues like diabetes, blood pressure, high cholesterol, fatty liver disease and weight management with Australia's first doctor and Dietitian designed, scientifically formulated, healthy home-delivered meals.

The company’s approach to weight loss assists customers to ‘reset’ their metabolisms and burn their own body fat for fuel. This is thanks to Be Fit Food’s proven low-carb, low-calorie wholefoods approach. The company has delivered over 3 million meals to date and has helped Australians lose a collective weight of 100 tonnes in body fat.

richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Problem

In Australia alone, almost 70% of people are overweight or obese and there is a new diabetes diagnosis every 5 minutes.

People often overlook the most simple of remedies when it comes to addressing health concerns, for example, food as the first medicine. The products individuals choose to nourish their bodies have a direct impact on their overall health and longevity and can either fuel or deplete their health.

Solution

Be Fit Food creates meals using the most up-to-date scientific evidence from around the world to ensure that Australians can eat themselves to better health. On average, Be Fit Food customers lose 5.89kg in 14 days on the company’s metabolism reset program using only wholefoods.

Differentiator

The company has developed scientifically formulated, doctor and dietitian designed meals specifically to improve health, so that food can be used as the first medicine to treat chronic health conditions such as obesity, diabetes, fatty liver disease, hypertension and hypercholesterolemia.

Intellectual property

Be Fit Food owns several trademarks in Australia including Be Fit Food, Carb to Protein Ratio, Food as the First Medicine, and Real Food, Fast Results. Its meal formula evolves with the scientific evidence to ensure that it is most effective in the treatment, management and prevention of chronic health conditions and boosts general health and overall well-being. The company has also invested in its own independently published study with Deakin University.

Addressable market

The market size, measured by revenue of the weight loss industry, was at $552.9M in 2022, with the actual indicated financial burden in Australia at $11.8 billion.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Growth Plan

Be Fit Food wants to capitalise on its current growth by entering new markets and industries such as hospitals, health professional outreach (GP’s, Bariatric Surgeons, Orthopaedic Surgeons), Aged Care and continue to expand our current retailer portfolio by gaining national distribution in all key accounts (Woolworths x 780+ stores already secured, IGA, Chemist Warehouse, Priceline, Terry White, Chemmart and Whole Life Pharmacy).

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Capital required

Be Fit Food is seeking to raise $500k to $2M through this equity raise. To date, its founders have bootstrapped the business.

Valuation Uplift

With funding from the current round being used to accelerate growth in national markets, distribution channels, NDIS accreditation and expanded partnerships with Health Insurers, Be Fit Food’s valuation is set to increase in future rounds.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Revenue Growth

Having generated $32.1M in revenue since starting, growing from $163,000 in 2016 to $6,204,000 in FY22, with 72% of revenue from direct online sales, Be Fit Food has sizzled with 351% YoY revenue growth.

The company is forecasting gross revenue of $24.5M in FY26 and an EBITDA of $3.5M (15%).
